        RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC is registered as an investment adviser with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) under the Investment Advisers Act of 1940. The firm's registration became effective following the filing and approval of its Form ADV with the SEC.
      </p>
      <p class="ds-body rv">
        <strong>SEC registration does not constitute an endorsement by the Commission, nor does it indicate that the adviser has attained a particular level of skill or ability.</strong> Registration simply means that the firm has met the requirements for registration and is subject to ongoing SEC oversight and examination.
      </p>

