    <!-- 02 ADVISORY RELATIONSHIP -->
    <div class="ds" id="advisory">
      <div class="ds-tag rv">02</div>
      <h2 class="ds-h rv">Nature of the<br><em>Advisory Relationship</em></h2>
      <p class="ds-body rv">
        RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC provides investment advisory services on a discretionary and non-discretionary basis to high-net-worth individuals, families, trusts, estates, and related entities. The firm acts as a <strong>fiduciary</strong> in all advisory relationships, meaning it is legally and ethically obligated to act solely in the best interests of its clients at all times.
      </p>

      <div class="warn-box rv">
        <div class="warn-label">Fiduciary Obligation</div>
        <p class="warn-text">As an SEC-registered investment adviser, RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC owes a fiduciary duty to each advisory client. This duty requires the firm to act with utmost good faith, to disclose all material conflicts of interest, and to provide only investment advice that it reasonably believes to be in the best interest of each client, given the client's individual financial circumstances, investment objectives, and risk tolerance.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="disc-list rv">
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Discretionary Management:</strong> In discretionary accounts, RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC has authority to make investment decisions on behalf of the client without prior approval for each transaction, subject to the investment policy statement and any written restrictions provided by the client.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Non-Discretionary Advice:</strong> In non-discretionary engagements, the firm provides investment recommendations and financial planning advice, but all final investment decisions rest with the client.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Suitability Assessment:</strong> Prior to providing advice, the firm conducts a thorough assessment of each client's financial situation, investment objectives, time horizon, liquidity needs, tax circumstances, and risk tolerance.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Ongoing Monitoring:</strong> For ongoing advisory relationships, the firm provides continuous monitoring of client portfolios and financial plans, with formal reviews conducted at least annually.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 03 INVESTMENT RISKS -->
    <div class="ds" id="risks">
      <div class="ds-tag rv">03</div>
      <h2 class="ds-h rv">Investment Risk<br><em>Disclosures</em></h2>
      <p class="ds-body rv">
        All investment strategies involve risk. The value of investments can decrease as well as increase, and clients may receive back less than the amount originally invested. Past performance is not a reliable indicator of future results. The following risks are material to investment strategies employed by RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC:
      </p>

      <div class="disc-list rv">
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Market Risk:</strong> The value of securities held in a portfolio may decline due to general market conditions, economic factors, geopolitical events, or changes in investor sentiment unrelated to the specific securities held.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Interest Rate Risk:</strong> Changes in interest rates can adversely affect the value of fixed income securities and interest-rate-sensitive investments. Rising interest rates generally cause the value of existing bonds to decline.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Credit Risk:</strong> The issuer of a debt security may be unable to make interest or principal payments, resulting in a loss of value. Credit risk is generally higher for securities rated below investment grade.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Liquidity Risk:</strong> Certain investments — including alternative investments, private equity, and thinly traded securities — may be difficult to sell at a fair price, or may be subject to lock-up periods that restrict redemption.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Concentration Risk:</strong> Portfolios that are concentrated in a limited number of securities, sectors, or geographies may experience greater volatility than broadly diversified portfolios.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Tax Risk:</strong> Changes in tax legislation, regulations, or their interpretation may affect the after-tax returns of investments and the tax efficiency of financial planning strategies.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Inflation Risk:</strong> The real value of investments may be eroded over time by inflation, particularly for fixed income securities and cash holdings with returns that do not keep pace with inflation.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Alternative Investment Risk:</strong> Private equity, hedge funds, real assets, and other alternative investments involve unique risks including illiquidity, leverage, limited regulatory oversight, complex fee structures, and reduced transparency compared to publicly traded securities.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="warn-box rv" style="margin-top:28px">
        <div class="warn-label">Performance Disclosure</div>
        <p class="warn-text">Any reference to performance — historical, projected, or illustrative — is not a guarantee of future results. Investment returns and principal value will fluctuate, and an investor's account value at any given time may be worth more or less than the original amount invested. RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC does not guarantee any specific level of performance or that any investment objective will be achieved.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 04 CONFLICTS OF INTEREST -->
    <div class="ds" id="conflicts">
      <div class="ds-tag rv">04</div>
      <h2 class="ds-h rv">Conflicts of<br><em>Interest</em></h2>
      <p class="ds-body rv">
        As a fiduciary, RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC is required to identify, disclose, and — where possible — eliminate material conflicts of interest. The firm takes this obligation seriously and structures its business to minimize conflicts. The following disclosures address conflicts that may be relevant to clients:
      </p>

      <div class="disc-list rv">
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Fee-Only Compensation:</strong> RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC is compensated solely by client fees based on assets under management or fixed financial planning fees. The firm does not receive commissions, 12b-1 fees, referral fees, or any other compensation from third parties for recommending specific investment products or services. This fee structure eliminates the most common source of conflicts in the investment advisory industry.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Related Party Transactions:</strong> The firm does not direct client assets into securities in which the firm or its principals have a financial interest without prior written disclosure to and consent from the affected client.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Allocation of Investment Opportunities:</strong> When similar investment opportunities are available to multiple clients, the firm follows a fair and equitable allocation policy. The firm's Form ADV Part 2A describes the allocation procedures in detail.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Outside Business Activities:</strong> Principals of the firm may engage in outside business activities. Material outside activities are disclosed in the firm's Form ADV and individual Form ADV Part 2B brochure supplements.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Soft Dollar Arrangements:</strong> The firm does not maintain soft dollar arrangements. Brokerage commissions are used solely to compensate executing brokers for trade execution services, consistent with the firm's duty to seek best execution for client transactions.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 05 FEES -->
    <div class="ds" id="fees">
      <div class="ds-tag rv">05</div>
      <h2 class="ds-h rv">Fee Structure &amp;<br><em>Compensation</em></h2>
      <p class="ds-body rv">
        RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC charges fees based on the value of assets under management (AUM) for ongoing investment advisory relationships, and fixed or hourly fees for standalone financial planning engagements. The firm's complete fee schedule is set forth in its Form ADV Part 2A, which is provided to all prospective clients prior to engagement.
      </p>

      <div class="disc-list rv">
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>AUM-Based Fees:</strong> Ongoing investment management fees are calculated as a percentage of assets under management, billed quarterly in advance or arrears as specified in the client agreement. The specific fee schedule applicable to each client is set forth in the executed investment advisory agreement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Financial Planning Fees:</strong> Fixed fees for comprehensive financial planning engagements are agreed upon in writing prior to the commencement of services, based on the scope and complexity of the engagement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Third-Party Costs:</strong> In addition to the firm's advisory fees, clients bear the costs of investment products held in their accounts, including mutual fund expense ratios, ETF fees, and brokerage commissions. These costs are separate from and in addition to RADIANX CAPITAL's advisory fees.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>Custodial Fees:</strong> Client assets are held in custody at third-party financial institutions. Custodians may charge account maintenance fees, transaction fees, and other charges. These fees are disclosed separately by the custodian and are not retained by RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="dl-item">
          <div class="dl-dash">—</div>
          <div class="dl-text"><strong>No Performance Fees:</strong> RADIANX CAPITAL, LLC does not charge performance-based fees except where specifically agreed to in writing with qualified clients meeting the definition under Rule 205-3 of the Investment Advisers Act of 1940.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="warn-box rv" style="margin-top:28px">
        <div class="warn-label">Higher Fees Disclosure</div>
        <p class="warn-text">A client could potentially achieve equivalent or lower-cost investment outcomes through direct investment in mutual funds, ETFs, or other investment vehicles without engaging an investment adviser. The value proposition of advisory services lies in the coordination, customisation, tax optimisation, and ongoing oversight that an adviser provides — not merely in access to investment products.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

